latestPosts.caption:
For as long as I remember I have loved fashion & the way clothes make you feel. I started as a fashion buyer & worked for high street retailers before professionally training as personal stylist in 2012. Since then I have worked with countless women & men to help them discover their style.
In the past 4-5 years my business has grown to a full time job. I am passionate about creating an environment where you leave every session feeling confident in yourself. 
From full-time Mums to busy executives, women returning to work to those whose children have flown the nest, following weight loss or gain, those who hate shopping or perhaps you’ve been through a life change. More often people tell me that they feel in a style rut, have lost a sense of themselves or feel overwhelmed with shopping. 
Using my knowledge & guidance I share advice on how to pull looks together from new & existing pieces in your wardrobe. I will show you how to style an outfit to flatter your body shape. I will get you to wear colours that suit you showing you colour combinations you may not of considered before. I advise you how to accessories your outfits & ensure you come away from every style consultation feeling fabulous. 
Working alongside a personal stylist will save you money in the long run, helping you avoid shopping mistakes by ensuring everything you purchase works for you, your body shape, your colours & your lifestyle. 

Anyways enough about me, how can I help you? 
Get in touch & let me know.

latestPosts.caption:
Reasons why you should work with a personal stylist

There are so many positive reasons to work with a personal stylist. Perhaps you think that investing in a Personal Stylist is unnecesary, but if you’ve been feeling stressed or less than happy with this area of your life, then it can have a huge positive impact on changing the way you feel about yourself and your wardrobe. And the end result is increased confidence. 

You will get a wardrobe that is full of pieces that work for you & fits into your lifestyle. You’ll have fewer clothes but more outfits you’ll love to wear. It will save precious time and look your absolute best daily. I will coach you into understanding more about your style & giving you the confidence to follow through with it. 

These are just some of the many reasons why if you feel stuck in a rut, if you hate your wardrobe you should get in touch now. We’ll work together to get you out of your style rut and into a style that makes you feel confident, saving you time and money along the way.

Whilst I don’t want to wish away the summer we haven’t had yet here in the UK it was very exciting to see the @hushofficial new AW range in person at the press event the other day. Since its rebrand 2 years ago Hush has gone on an exciting journey of rediscovering its customer & showcasing some amazing pieces in their ranges. Pieces I’ve been shopping for my clients & myself. 

Looking ahead for AW I’m excited about their denim ranges having just bought my first pair - the white Cordelia - and love them. They have lots of colour in knits, fabrics such as suede & key pieces that will be your go-to’s in autumn. I’m excited & you should be too! Watch this space

This UK changeable weather has defiantly made it harder to dress. Oh how we want summer so badly but we seem to be stuck in autumn. So having a wardrobe that is versatile & can service me & my lifestyle is so important. Being able to pick out pieces that work for not just the weather but events / social occasions makes getting dressed so much easier.

Yesterday I was invited to the @hushofficial press day in London where I got a sneak peak of their AW collection. It made me feel all nostalgic about my old buying days seeing clothes set out for the season & not to wish right now away but there are some super exciting pieces from Hush coming up! 

I got these Cordelia white jeans a few weeks ago & they are fast becoming my favs. Comfort & leg shape are key & these jeans tick both boxes!
